FBIS3-2395 "drchi046_p_94009" FBIS-CHI-94-046 Document Type:Daily Report 9 Mar 1994 Central-South Region Plans To Clear Illegal Buildings in Hebei Capital OW0403031094 Beijing XINHUA in English 0239 GMT 4 Mar 94 OW0403031094 Beijing XINHUA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Shijiazhuang, March 4 (XINHUA) -- The former royal summer resort of Chengde city in north China's Hebei Province will finally get rid of the many illegal buildings that affect its historical and natural beauties. Local officials said all the 29 illegal modern buildings, totaling 81,000 sq m in the former summer retreat of emperors of the Qing Dynasty (1644-1911) will soon be removed. The 560-ha resort is under the protection of the national government. It attracts tens of thousands of tourists every year from both at home and abroad. Already, the sources said, eight illegal buildings, including residential houses of city officials and an office building of the city bureau of cultural relics, have been removed. According to the sources, all the removal work will be completed before this year's tourism season arrives.
